data.title: Enabling horizontal scroll for project list in project manager
Fix missing and incorrect values in return value of _move method
Fix broken stream reading in StreamPeerBuffer
data.body: StreamPeerBuffer was not using or advancing the stream position when reading data from its array. Now it does. Address #10293.

data.title: Project manager UI displaced by long paths #10245
StreamPeerBuffer is broken
data.body:
**Operating system or device - Godot version:**
Debian GNU / Linux, Godot 3 alpha1

**Issue description:**
Putting data in a StreamPeerBuffer and reading it back out produces different results


**Steps to reproduce:**
Put this code in a node and run the scene:
```
extends Node

func _ready():
	if not test_read_write_equals_unsigned():
		print("Failed read write equals for unsigned ints")

func test_read_write_equals_unsigned():
	var buf = StreamPeerBuffer.new()
	buf.put_u8(69)
	buf.put_u16(420)
	buf.put_u32(123454321)
	
	var data = buf.get_data_array()
	var buf2 = StreamPeerBuffer.new()
	buf2.set_data_array(data)
	
	print(buf2.get_u8())
	print(buf2.get_u16())
	print(buf2.get_u32())
```

Output:
```
69
57088
65280
Failed read write equals for unsigned ints

```

data.title: Metallic Texture is not rendering properly.

Mirror material in Materials demo is not reflecting the HDR environment correctly, rendering mostly red,green and blue in dark regions.

Opening the Material Tester demo, running the demo and viewing the mirror mesh.
